<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3487] Full support for newer Delphi versions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3487</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a few issues with newer Delphi versions, in particular regarding the deprecated sockets library that we use today. Currently, the sockets support has been removed from the Thrift Delphi bindings for newer Delphi versions, so we are at least able to compile the rest w/o problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If sockets are needed, one may consider downloading the file &lt;a href=&quot;http://sourceforge.net/p/radstudiodemos/code/HEAD/tree/branches/RadStudio_XE8/Object%20Pascal/VCL/InetWinSockets/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Web.Win.Sockets from the RAD-Studio Samples&lt;/a&gt; instead to reactivate the old behaviour. However, this is not a recommended solution, only a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
