                            <comment id="15054234" author="jensg" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2015 11:14:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, know that issue. If you maybe already have a patch ready, feel free to submit. I&apos;d gladly review it. If possible, don&apos;t break compatibility with older Delphi versions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15065337" author="jensg" created="Sat, 19 Dec 2015 11:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12778687/12778687_THRIFT-3487-Full-support-for-newer-Delphi-versions.patch&quot; title=&quot;THRIFT-3487-Full-support-for-newer-Delphi-versions.patch attached to THRIFT-3487&quot;&gt;This patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; contains:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fix for FStream.Seek() now expecting an UInt64 instead of Int64&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;workaround to (temporarily) exclude socket support from newer versions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;TODO: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;socket support needs to be revised for newer versions, the old sockets are deprecated and (usually) not available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15065339" author="jensg" created="Sat, 19 Dec 2015 11:13:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, but leaving ticket open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15246453" author="kylej61782" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2016 20:19:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should add the required code to support sockets in the newer Delphi versions.  It&apos;s heavily inspired (read: basically a direct translation) of the sockets code found in the C++ library.  I tested it with the provided tests and everything seemed to be on the up and up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15248835" author="jensg" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 22:48:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, slightly improved &amp;amp; committed. Cool, now we have full socket support again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15248837" author="jensg" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 22:50:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12799617/12799617_0001-THRIFT-3487-Full-support-for-newer-Delphi-versions.patch&quot; title=&quot;0001-THRIFT-3487-Full-support-for-newer-Delphi-versions.patch attached to THRIFT-3487&quot;&gt;Committed version&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
